  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe modal presentation we currently use doesn't conform to iOS interface guidelines and can be optimised by using the [Stack Presentation found in latest React Navigation](https://twitter.com/satya164/status/1142786047245467649?lang=en). Stacks allow dismissing by a swipe gesture and introduce an animation that more accurately portrays the spatial relationship of a modal to rest of the app layout.\r\n\r\n![Screen Recording (Xcode)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/73290680-23b8c900-41ff-11ea-914d-5ba03e980273.gif)\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nChange iOS modal presentation to Stack Presentation, found in latest React Navigation. Refactor current modals to use the new presentation mode. Modals should follow the native behaviour: allow dragging away to dismiss with a specific `x` button to dismiss.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nAll modals on iOS use the stack presentation and not the legacy slide from the bottom approach. Slide from the bottom remains the Android default.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nFor reference,[ a Stack modal presentation in Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=6238%3A813)\r\n\r\nthanks! üôè \r\n",
